  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NBS Bank Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(i) Growth of SMEs in Malawi through increased access to financial services; 
(ii) Growth of the Bank as the investment will allow further leveraging; and 
(iii) Demonstration effect, allowing further investment by other players into the Malawian SME segment.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NBS Bank Limited (NBS or the Bank) plans to raise ordinary equity capital of up to $10 million through a combination of a rights issue and private placement to IFC. IFCs proposed investment will consist of a straight equity investment of up to $10.0 million. 

The proposed project intends to strengthen the Banks capitalization and expand its capacity to sustainably manage its growth, especially in its SME target market segment.</narrative>
  </description>
